From f2aed267ee231db5cc8102042a40f5ecd4b138a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ed Beroset <beroset@ieee.org>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 15:12:49 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Remove spurious line from Kconfig

This removes a line with a single `.` character that caused bitbake to
emit an error.  The error is:
ERROR: linux-anthias-3.10.40+marshmallow-r0 do_kernel_configcheck: config analysis failed when running 'symbol_why.py --dotconfig /home/ejb/asteroid/build/tmp/work-shared/anthias/kernel-source/.config --mismatches --classify'

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate
Signed-off-by: Ed Beroset <beroset@ieee.org>
---
 drivers/media/usb/stk1160/Kconfig | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/usb/stk1160/Kconfig b/drivers/media/usb/stk1160/Kconfig
index 1c3a1ec00237..5fc9c2c354b8 100644
--- a/drivers/media/usb/stk1160/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/media/usb/stk1160/Kconfig
@@ -17,4 +17,3 @@ config VIDEO_STK1160_AC97
 
 	---help---
 	  Enables AC97 codec support for stk1160 driver.
-.
